WEBVTT


00:00:00.288 --> 00:00:03.247
is your workplace ACTUALLY diverse and inclusive?

00:00:03.248 --> 00:00:04.847
or are they just saying that?

00:00:04.848 --> 00:00:07.011
here are five questions to help you figure that out

00:00:07.248 --> 00:00:09.647
no 1 leadership m: what does that look like?

00:00:09.648 --> 00:00:10.521
it's not a great

00:00:10.522 --> 00:00:14.575
sign if it looks like certain groups are completely locked out of leadership positions

00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:16.389
no 2 is there a formal process

00:00:16.390 --> 00:00:20.705
like a survey for employees to safely provide feedback to management and leadership?

00:00:21.026 --> 00:00:23.351
no 3 do they publicly commit to

00:00:23.352 --> 00:00:28.349
diversity equity and inclusion and things like their mission vision or valley statements?

00:00:28.350 --> 00:00:30.818
no 4 if you're in a management position

00:00:30.819 --> 00:00:35.218
did you ever receive training on how to Foster diversity and inclusion as a leader?

00:00:35.339 --> 00:00:37.220
last but not least no 5

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:40.880
during meetings what happens if some employees talk over others?

00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:44.260
do leaders make an effort to make sure that all voices are heard?

00:00:45.020 --> 00:00:46.739
now that you've asked yourself those questions

00:00:46.740 --> 00:00:48.019
how did your workplace do?

00:00:48.020 --> 00:00:49.280
let us know in the comments
